Afghanistan, Kosovo, Chechnya.

297
00:32:20,188 --> 00:32:24,591
I am what psychologists would call
alpha male.

298
00:32:26,828 --> 00:32:28,591
I know how these people think.

299
00:32:32,967 --> 00:32:34,958
I am a trained killer myself.

300
00:32:36,871 --> 00:32:38,805
- What?
- I'm a trained killer.

301
00:32:40,108 --> 00:32:44,738
No, seriously, I am. Don't worry.

302
00:32:47,982 --> 00:32:49,813
I know what I am talking about.

303
00:32:50,351 --> 00:32:51,818
<i>Combat Weekly?</i>

304
00:32:51,986 --> 00:32:55,251
I will get us all out of here.

305
00:32:58,092 --> 00:33:01,755
- So this is what, a mummy?
- No, it is not a mummy.

306
00:33:01,929 --> 00:33:04,056
The skin's practically still warm.

307
00:33:04,232 --> 00:33:05,426
Oh.

308
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:09,969
- So who do you think did this?
- Whoever cut the kid's head off, obviously.

309
00:33:12,206 --> 00:33:15,869
God only knows who we been
talking to, but it wasn't the police.

310
00:33:16,044 --> 00:33:19,605
Listen. You hear anything?

311
00:33:19,781 --> 00:33:22,306
There's no sirens.
In a normal hostage situation...

312
00:33:22,483 --> 00:33:25,179
...the whole block would be packed
with emergency services.

313
00:33:25,353 --> 00:33:27,617
It would sound like the Fourth of July
out there.

314
00:33:28,122 --> 00:33:30,750
I don't think this robbery's
even been reported.

315
00:33:31,092 --> 00:33:33,424
So according to you,
the police, the real police...

316
00:33:33,594 --> 00:33:35,061
...they do not know we're here?

317
00:33:35,229 --> 00:33:37,789
No. Maybe. I don't know.

318
00:33:38,433 --> 00:33:40,424
What kind of floor is this anyway?

319
00:33:41,135 --> 00:33:42,830
So things are looking up.

320
00:33:43,004 --> 00:33:45,370
- Look at it, Peter.
- So?

321
00:33:45,540 --> 00:33:46,700
Jesus Christ.

322
00:33:46,874 --> 00:33:48,398
Okay, okay, okay. I understand...

323
00:33:48,576 --> 00:33:51,773
...but things could be a lot worse.

324
00:33:51,979 --> 00:33:55,380
If the police don't know we're here,
all we do is grab Yuri and leave.

325
00:33:55,550 --> 00:33:59,008
- It's that simple, is it?
- What could go wrong? Ha-ha.

326
00:33:59,187 --> 00:34:02,020
What are they going to do?

327
00:34:04,992 --> 00:34:06,289
Are you ready for war?

328
00:34:07,562 --> 00:34:10,895
Dmitry, they're harmless.

329
00:34:12,266 --> 00:34:15,895
Anna, it's possible you have anything
we can use as weapon?

330
00:34:28,916 --> 00:34:33,046
- You best keep hold of that for yourself.
- I will.

331
00:34:34,689 --> 00:34:38,352
The only other thing we could use
is that.

332
00:34:41,963 --> 00:34:43,760
That is enough.

333
00:34:45,767 --> 00:34:47,894
In trained hands...

334
00:34:49,003 --> 00:34:51,096
...a filing cabinet...

335
00:34:52,006 --> 00:34:54,531
...can be more effective than a tank.

336
00:34:54,709 --> 00:34:57,940
- What?
- Wait, Dmitry. Help me, beside door.

337
00:35:01,015 --> 00:35:02,448
On two, up.

338
00:35:05,453 --> 00:35:08,786
Up, Dmitry, up. Good.

339
00:35:10,591 --> 00:35:15,028
Turn round. Turn round, comrade.
Be strong. Be strong.

340
00:35:21,702 --> 00:35:23,329
Yes.

341
00:35:23,805 --> 00:35:24,897
This is plan.

342
00:35:25,306 --> 00:35:29,037
Anna, you bang the door:
Bang, bang, bang.

343
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:33,476
When they open the door, Dmitry and me,
we push filing cabinet on top of leader.

344
00:35:33,648 --> 00:35:38,642
He goes down, we jump second man.
You, you take gun from leader.

345
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:42,119
If you want, kick him in head.

346
00:35:43,157 --> 00:35:46,718
- This is suicide.
- Suicide?

347
00:35:47,195 --> 00:35:48,992
It's better than being murdered, no?

348
00:35:51,065 --> 00:35:53,966
- Yeah.
- The army taught me that.

349
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:57,037
Good luck.

350
00:36:03,978 --> 00:36:05,502
No!

351
00:36:08,816 --> 00:36:10,078
What are you doing, man?

352
00:36:13,521 --> 00:36:18,083
You make a big mistake trying
to bite me, pal.

353
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:21,820
Now it's time to pay the price.
Aah...

354
00:36:21,996 --> 00:36:23,258
That's it.

355
00:36:24,232 --> 00:36:25,859
Don't, Peter, don't.

356
00:36:26,033 --> 00:36:27,330
- Why not?
- Just don't.

357
00:36:27,501 --> 00:36:30,299
What, Ritchie, you're animal lover?

358
00:36:31,038 --> 00:36:34,439
- Get that thing away from me, all right?
- Ha-ha-ha.

359
00:36:34,609 --> 00:36:37,942
Aah! Bastard.

360
00:36:41,182 --> 00:36:43,116
Help.
- Yuri's in there.

361
00:36:43,284 --> 00:36:45,275
Open the door!

362
00:36:46,053 --> 00:36:48,749
- Help. Help us.
- Dmitry, don't worry. This is good plan.

363
00:36:48,923 --> 00:36:51,255
We'll probably get away
with 50 percent casualties.

364
00:36:51,425 --> 00:36:53,393
- Open the door.
- But there are three of us.

365
00:36:53,561 --> 00:36:56,553
Help! Please!

366
00:36:57,098 --> 00:36:59,828
Please help us! Help!

367
00:37:01,869 --> 00:37:05,236
Let us out of here, please.

368
00:37:06,741 --> 00:37:09,039
No more Mr. Nice Guy.

369
00:37:10,711 --> 00:37:15,205
Yuri, Yuri, what is all that banging?
I thought you were being cut up.

370
00:37:16,617 --> 00:37:19,484
- What the fuck are you up to?
- It was a trap.

371
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:22,812
They were going to push that on you
when you came in.

372
00:37:23,591 --> 00:37:25,923
You, come here.

373
00:37:32,733 --> 00:37:36,760
Yuri, take this. Change of plan.
We're leaving.

374
00:37:37,138 --> 00:37:39,732
Goodbye, everybody. It's been fun.

375
00:37:40,207 --> 00:37:41,834
- Come on.
Hey, we can't do this.

376
00:37:43,778 --> 00:37:46,042
- What?
- We can't leave.

377
00:37:46,213 --> 00:37:49,182
- Why the fuck not?
- You know why.

378
00:37:49,583 --> 00:37:52,074
What do you care
about these fucking idiots?

379
00:37:52,420 --> 00:37:53,785
What idiots?

380
00:37:53,955 --> 00:37:55,946
We're gonna figure something out,
all right?

381
00:37:56,123 --> 00:37:58,023
I'm a thief. I'm not a murderer.

382
00:37:58,192 --> 00:38:00,752
- Listen, you stay, I'm going.
- Can I see that?

383
00:38:00,928 --> 00:38:02,953
You're not going
until we figure this out.

384
00:38:03,130 --> 00:38:08,659
- You going to stop me, Ritchie? Huh?
- Lf I have to, yeah.

385
00:38:19,313 --> 00:38:20,712
Come on, come...

386
00:38:34,228 --> 00:38:36,958
What the fuck are you looking at?

387
00:38:38,399 --> 00:38:40,731
Fucking idiot, Yuri.

388
00:38:41,969 --> 00:38:43,561
Drop it.

389
00:38:44,472 --> 00:38:46,303
Drop it.

390
00:38:47,308 --> 00:38:51,745
Katerina, get the gun.
Helena, get the bag and the shotgun.

391
00:38:55,583 --> 00:38:57,050
Do not be afraid.

392
00:38:57,218 --> 00:38:59,812
This is all part of the Almighty's plan.

393
00:38:59,987 --> 00:39:01,614
- I'll call the police.
- Get back.

394
00:39:01,789 --> 00:39:03,484
- The Almighty's in charge now.
- But...

395
00:39:03,657 --> 00:39:06,182
- Get back in here, you whore.
- Okay, lady, listen...

396
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,328
Speak again
and I'll shoot you in the head.

397
00:39:08,496 --> 00:39:10,623
Yuri, get that walkie-talkie.

398
00:39:11,999 --> 00:39:15,628
Let us thank the Almighty
for delivering us from this evil.

399
00:39:15,803 --> 00:39:17,998
On your knees.

400
00:39:24,612 --> 00:39:25,704
YURl:
What was that?

401
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:29,145
That's what I was trying to tell...
Jesus Christ.

402
00:39:29,316 --> 00:39:30,977
I told you to be quiet.

403
00:39:32,286 --> 00:39:33,753
Let's go.

404
00:39:36,891 --> 00:39:38,825
Try anything
and you will be slaughtered.

405
00:39:41,062 --> 00:39:44,657
Can't believe this. Fucking Russia.

406
00:40:07,188 --> 00:40:09,622
- Sonya.
- Do not be afraid.

407
00:40:09,790 --> 00:40:12,850
- But it came from down there.
- Stay here.

408
00:40:13,260 --> 00:40:16,195
Don't go.
You don't know what's down there.

409
00:40:16,363 --> 00:40:20,959
I have no fear.
The Almighty will protect me.

410
00:40:51,198 --> 00:40:55,157
I was really impressed with the way
you performed our operation.

411
00:40:55,436 --> 00:40:59,566
Unlike some,
you acted with great courage.

412
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:02,201
If we make it out of here...

413
00:41:03,677 --> 00:41:05,702
...I'd really like to take you for drink.

414
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:06,904
What?

415
00:41:08,382 --> 00:41:11,874
No, I was just saying...

416
00:41:12,052 --> 00:41:14,612
...if we don't all end up dead...

417
00:41:14,855 --> 00:41:16,447
...maybe we could go for drink.

418
00:41:16,624 --> 00:41:20,219
- As a group?
- Just you and me.

419
00:41:22,763 --> 00:41:24,230
No.

420
00:41:30,404 --> 00:41:32,395
No, don't.

421
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,872
From now on, I don't want nothing
to do with you, Dmitry.

422
00:41:36,043 --> 00:41:40,412
- You... You deserter, you.
- I'm sorry, okay?

423
00:41:41,248 --> 00:41:42,681
I was scared.

424
00:41:43,217 --> 00:41:46,584
I know you'll think I'm not a real man
for saying this...

425
00:41:46,754 --> 00:41:50,246
...but I don't like violence. I never have.

426
00:41:50,424 --> 00:41:52,187
I can't say I understand you.

427
00:41:53,561 --> 00:41:57,088
Fear, being frightened, afraidness...

428
00:41:57,264 --> 00:42:00,256
...these words are not part
of Boris' vocabulary.

429
00:42:00,434 --> 00:42:03,767
I am an alpha male,
but then I can't blame you.

430
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:06,805
I suppose I did spend 15 years in army.

431
00:42:09,610 --> 00:42:11,908
It was the time of my life.

432
00:42:12,279 --> 00:42:15,146
It's not like you journalists say,
that it's just bullying...

433
00:42:15,316 --> 00:42:17,113
...cannibalism and homosexual rape.

434
00:42:18,919 --> 00:42:21,547
The sense of camaraderie
is unbelievable.

435
00:42:21,889 --> 00:42:25,325
Imagine being a part of the biggest family
in the whole world.

436
00:42:25,793 --> 00:42:28,421
That's what being in the army was like.

437
00:42:29,163 --> 00:42:33,896
I'm not ashamed to say that I loved every
single man in my regiment.

438
00:42:35,703 --> 00:42:37,568
And why did you leave?

439
00:42:38,239 --> 00:42:42,403
I was accused of bullying, cannibalism
and homosexual rape.

440
00:42:42,576 --> 00:42:44,407
I did not do it, of course, Dmitry.

441
00:42:44,578 --> 00:42:47,172
Them bastards in my regiment
set me up.

442
00:42:51,218 --> 00:42:52,685
Not so tough now, are we?

443
00:42:53,821 --> 00:42:55,379
What?

444
00:43:00,594 --> 00:43:03,586
One more step and I'll break you in two.

445
00:43:11,138 --> 00:43:13,129
He knows who's boss.

446
00:43:22,616 --> 00:43:25,551
- What was making that noise?
- There is nothing to fear.

447
00:43:25,719 --> 00:43:27,619
This is a sacred place.

448
00:43:28,589 --> 00:43:30,887
I know what the Almighty
wants us to do.

449
00:43:32,126 --> 00:43:36,961
- And that would be...?
- It's time to make a sacrifice.

450
00:43:43,137 --> 00:43:44,434
Well...

451
00:43:44,605 --> 00:43:47,506
...looks like we're all
in the same boat here.

452
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:51,375
And if we wanna make it out of here,
we better make a truce.

453
00:43:51,545 --> 00:43:54,776
For what it's worth, it was never
part of the plan to take hostages.

454
00:43:54,948 --> 00:43:57,883
- I'm sorry.
- We know what you did.

455
00:43:58,052 --> 00:44:02,489
- Why did you cut his head off?
- I didn't cut anybody's head off.

456
00:44:02,656 --> 00:44:03,748
Neither did he.

457
00:44:04,558 --> 00:44:07,823
There's someone else here, guys, all right?
We're not alone here.

458
00:44:07,995 --> 00:44:11,658
I don't know who it is, but he's the guy
who cut the kid's head off.

459
00:44:11,999 --> 00:44:14,968
My advice is get good lawyer.
Because when the police come...

460
00:44:15,135 --> 00:44:18,730
The police aren't coming.
The police don't even know we're here.

461
00:44:18,906 --> 00:44:20,498
Frankly, I wish they did.

462
00:44:20,674 --> 00:44:24,667
Now, whoever killed that kid,
he stopped the lift as well.

463
00:44:24,845 --> 00:44:27,405
He pretended to be the police
so we'd send a hostage.

464
00:44:27,581 --> 00:44:29,913
And, well, you know what happened.

465
00:44:30,784 --> 00:44:32,479
You're a security guard, right?

466
00:44:33,087 --> 00:44:36,352
- Yes.
- You've seen this floor before?

467
00:44:42,496 --> 00:44:43,963
Who wants to be saved first?

468
00:44:44,131 --> 00:44:46,964
What exactly do you mean
by being saved?

469
00:44:47,134 --> 00:44:48,294
You, get up.

470
00:44:54,341 --> 00:44:55,501
Mm-mm.

471
00:45:13,660 --> 00:45:16,185
