00:46:39,746 --> 00:46:43,273
Sonya told me to stay here
and not let you escape.

479
00:46:46,954 --> 00:46:50,253
But you know I've not done
anything wrong.

480
00:46:51,658 --> 00:46:54,252
This whole thing is a job for the police.

481
00:46:54,428 --> 00:46:57,056
Let us out
and we can call them together.

482
00:46:58,131 --> 00:47:00,292
But I'm just so scared.

483
00:47:01,134 --> 00:47:04,900
I'm scared too,
but this can all be over soon.

484
00:47:05,772 --> 00:47:07,637
Open the door.

485
00:47:10,344 --> 00:47:12,744
You promise to call the police?

486
00:47:14,248 --> 00:47:15,613
I promise.

487
00:47:16,850 --> 00:47:19,341
Everything's going to be okay.

488
00:48:02,062 --> 00:48:03,461
What?

489
00:48:04,131 --> 00:48:07,066
You know how to use a shotgun?
Take it.

490
00:48:07,935 --> 00:48:08,959
No.

491
00:48:09,136 --> 00:48:11,900
The reason I've got it
is because I'm the only one who does.

492
00:48:12,072 --> 00:48:13,903
I know how to use it.

493
00:48:14,841 --> 00:48:17,309
Yeah. Come on.

494
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:03,679
Dmitry, don't move.
I get the ropes off you.

495
00:49:04,491 --> 00:49:06,823
One, two...

496
00:49:11,365 --> 00:49:12,855
Dmitry?

497
00:49:14,568 --> 00:49:17,731
- What is it?
- There are no buttons.

498
00:49:18,972 --> 00:49:20,963
What was that?

499
00:49:22,709 --> 00:49:24,768
We can't call the lift.
There are no buttons.

500
00:49:24,945 --> 00:49:27,709
We're stuck here? Jesus Christ.
If we can't call the lift...

501
00:49:27,881 --> 00:49:30,213
...we're as good as dead.
- Just relax, relax.

502
00:49:30,384 --> 00:49:33,251
I can still get us out of here.
I gotta get this panel off.

503
00:49:33,420 --> 00:49:35,911
I'll short the system
and it will call the lift.

504
00:49:38,225 --> 00:49:39,715
That's it. We're all going to die.

505
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:44,227
We're going to be hunted down like animals
and killed one by one.

506
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:46,889
I mean, think about it.
What if he's a sex criminal?

507
00:49:47,067 --> 00:49:50,161
Dmitry, you are becoming hysterical.
I am now going to slap you.

508
00:49:50,337 --> 00:49:52,737
That's enough.
Nobody's getting slapped.

509
00:49:52,906 --> 00:49:55,500
We're all going to die
and he wants to slap me.

510
00:49:55,842 --> 00:49:59,869
- That's not fair.
- Where are you going?

511
00:50:00,047 --> 00:50:02,845
I'm gonna find a way to raise that thing
and get out of here.

512
00:50:03,016 --> 00:50:04,278
You coming?

513
00:50:12,225 --> 00:50:16,161
- Sonya?
- I didn't give you permission to speak.

514
00:50:20,267 --> 00:50:22,201
I need to see Helena.

515
00:50:43,990 --> 00:50:45,958
Room cleared and secured.

516
00:50:54,835 --> 00:50:57,030
No, Katerina. Stay.

517
00:50:57,904 --> 00:50:59,838
Helena, what happened?

518
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:08,680
- Answer me. What happened?
- I'm sorry. I was going to let them out.

519
00:51:09,316 --> 00:51:11,045
Please.

520
00:51:11,485 --> 00:51:13,715
- I'm sorry.
- Come.

521
00:51:14,654 --> 00:51:16,918
Yuri. Aah...

522
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:32,396
Get away from the door.

523
00:51:38,411 --> 00:51:40,538
Aah!
Come on.

524
00:51:41,815 --> 00:51:43,248
Aah!

525
00:51:45,385 --> 00:51:47,250
He's been shot. We've got to leave him.

526
00:51:47,454 --> 00:51:50,355
I haven't been shot, you idiot.
It's a cramp.

527
00:51:52,559 --> 00:51:55,255
- I'll stay.
- To hell with you.

528
00:52:20,020 --> 00:52:26,516
Boris, you have made fool of yourself.
Never leave man down.

529
00:52:26,960 --> 00:52:29,622
I can't believe you forgot that.

530
00:52:33,099 --> 00:52:34,930
Shh.

531
00:52:35,535 --> 00:52:37,366
Do you have anything for a weapon?

532
00:52:37,537 --> 00:52:39,095
I have a nail file.

533
00:52:39,272 --> 00:52:40,933
Great.

534
00:52:46,313 --> 00:52:47,974
Don't worry. Boris is back.

535
00:52:48,148 --> 00:52:50,776
Shh. Shut up.
- No, no, no. I'm ready to fight.

536
00:52:50,951 --> 00:52:54,478
- Point me in dire... Mm...
Just shut it.

537
00:52:55,555 --> 00:53:00,185
Yeah. It's a dud. Shit.

538
00:53:00,360 --> 00:53:04,126
- There's one round between us all.
- Where's Dmitry?

539
00:53:05,632 --> 00:53:10,228
Can anybody hear me?
Can anybody hear me?

540
00:53:10,403 --> 00:53:12,928
<i>Greetings, comrade.
- Oh, thank God.</i>

541
00:53:13,773 --> 00:53:17,504
You have to get the police.
Various people are trying to kill me.

542
00:53:17,677 --> 00:53:19,941
<i>What is your handle?</i>

543
00:53:20,113 --> 00:53:21,137
Huh?

544
00:53:21,314 --> 00:53:25,182
<i>- I said, what is your handle?
- I don't have a handle.</i>

545
00:53:25,652 --> 00:53:28,849
<i>- I don't have a handle.
- Oh, you've got to have handle.</i>

546
00:53:29,222 --> 00:53:31,520
<i>- Mine is...
- I don't want to know your handle.</i>

547
00:53:31,691 --> 00:53:32,988
Just listen.

548
00:53:33,159 --> 00:53:35,684
I got on this lift,
and you're probably thinking:

549
00:53:35,862 --> 00:53:38,626
"Normal passengers.
Ground floor, please. " No.

550
00:53:38,965 --> 00:53:42,025
Three of them had done a robbery
and the rest of us were hostages.

551
00:53:42,202 --> 00:53:43,726
Things have changed since then.

552
00:53:43,904 --> 00:53:48,739
Some of the hostages have taken over.
Yeah, they tried to sacrifice me.

553
00:53:48,909 --> 00:53:50,740
Come back, robbers, all is forgiven.

554
00:53:50,911 --> 00:53:55,211
And before I forget, there's also this
psycho, definite-sex-criminal nut job...

555
00:53:55,382 --> 00:53:57,714
...running around
cutting people's heads off.

556
00:53:57,884 --> 00:54:01,650
I haven't had the chance to talk to him yet,
but I'm sure I will later.

557
00:54:02,989 --> 00:54:06,186
<i>- Do you want to know what my handle is?
- What?</i>

558
00:54:06,359 --> 00:54:08,190
Didn't you hear a word I just said?

559
00:54:08,862 --> 00:54:11,956
<i>Oh, if you don't want to know,
I'll tell you anyway.</i>

560
00:54:12,132 --> 00:54:16,068
<i>- My handle is "Ferret. "
- Oh...</i>

561
00:54:16,236 --> 00:54:19,672
Listen, you weirdo.
Just phone the police.

562
00:54:21,908 --> 00:54:23,500
Hello?

563
00:54:25,312 --> 00:54:26,939
Ferret?

564
00:54:59,646 --> 00:55:00,874
Are you okay?

565
00:55:01,915 --> 00:55:06,477
- Dmitry, where are your trousers?
- Where I left them.

566
00:55:17,998 --> 00:55:21,161
That was me.
Just give me a second.

567
00:55:54,734 --> 00:55:57,828
Anna, you look closely,
you see blood on hook.

568
00:55:58,004 --> 00:56:00,438
I'm really glad you told me that.

569
00:56:09,049 --> 00:56:11,540
Dmitry, you hungry?

570
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:18,454
Look at that.

571
00:56:20,994 --> 00:56:22,985
Is that what I think it is?

572
00:56:29,436 --> 00:56:32,200
Dmitry, give me hand, please.

573
00:56:34,407 --> 00:56:36,307
"Chosen by God...

574
00:56:36,676 --> 00:56:40,737
...first czar of all the Russias,
defender of the one true faith...

575
00:56:41,014 --> 00:56:43,175
...and scourge of nonbelievers.

576
00:56:44,651 --> 00:56:46,812
Ivan the Terrible. "

577
00:57:06,706 --> 00:57:10,506
- And the Almighty can do anything?
- Yes. The Almighty is all-powerful.

578
00:57:10,677 --> 00:57:14,408
- And he can't die?
- Yes, Yuri, the Almighty is immortal.

579
00:57:14,581 --> 00:57:17,049
So that means he can't kill himself.

580
00:57:19,319 --> 00:57:21,844
Because if he can't kill himself...

581
00:57:22,021 --> 00:57:26,890
...then that means he's not all-powerful,
doesn't it?

582
00:57:30,130 --> 00:57:32,690
- Why don't we go and ask him?
- Oh.

583
00:57:34,567 --> 00:57:37,536
- I suppose we could.
- Yes. Let's do it now.

584
00:57:38,638 --> 00:57:42,130
- You stay and pray.
- But I want to meet the Almighty too.

585
00:57:42,308 --> 00:57:45,209
Be patient. Your time will come.

586
00:57:48,515 --> 00:57:50,210
Bye-bye.

587
00:57:51,117 --> 00:57:52,550
Look.

588
00:57:52,719 --> 00:57:56,052
"This cross is a symbol
of Ivan's almighty power...

589
00:57:56,222 --> 00:57:58,816
...and it will pass down
through the generations...

590
00:57:58,992 --> 00:58:02,519
...until there comes a time
when he will be made flesh again...

591
00:58:02,695 --> 00:58:05,095
...and save the souls of all.

592
00:58:05,465 --> 00:58:07,296
That time has come. "

593
00:58:10,403 --> 00:58:11,893
Hey.

594
00:58:12,505 --> 00:58:14,166
Remind you of anyone?

595
00:58:43,169 --> 00:58:46,627
Are you God?

596
00:58:48,775 --> 00:58:49,833
No.

597
00:58:51,144 --> 00:58:53,203
I am the devil!

598
00:59:48,268 --> 00:59:50,429
Peter!

599
00:59:58,144 --> 00:59:59,839
So let me get this straight.

600
01:00:00,013 --> 01:00:05,110
That witch with the Bible
is related to a wannabe Ivan the Terrible?

601
01:00:05,285 --> 01:00:08,777
- Yes.
- And they chop people up on this floor?

602
01:00:08,955 --> 01:00:10,582
You saw the fridge, right?

603
01:00:10,757 --> 01:00:14,420
They got a system here rigged above
and beyond what the normal security is.

604
01:00:14,861 --> 01:00:18,092
I mean, they must control the elevators,
the cameras, everything.

605
01:00:18,264 --> 01:00:22,223
- But how can they do this?
- Because they own the building.

606
01:00:25,605 --> 01:00:29,974
- They're the ones I ripped off.
- What did you steal?

607
01:00:31,611 --> 01:00:33,272
The cross.

608
01:00:34,480 --> 01:00:36,380
Ha-ha-ha. That's perfect.

609
01:00:36,549 --> 01:00:42,283
You stole a sacred relic from the insane
descendants of Ivan the Terrible.

610
01:00:42,922 --> 01:00:46,756
Give me the bag.
Give me the bag, I make drop-off.

611
01:00:46,926 --> 01:00:49,486
- What drop-off?
- It's simple.

612
01:00:49,662 --> 01:00:53,928
I return the cross, they let us go.
Therefore, the bag.

613
01:00:54,801 --> 01:00:56,393
Are you not hearing what we said?

614
01:00:56,569 --> 01:00:59,595
They're psycho twins.
They're not gonna let any of us leave...

615
01:00:59,772 --> 01:01:02,741
...with or without the cross.
- But I have negotiation skills.

616
01:01:02,909 --> 01:01:04,570
Now give me the bag.

617
01:01:13,419 --> 01:01:17,617
- It's beautiful.
- It's not the cross, you idiot.

618
01:01:18,658 --> 01:01:20,956
Peter, you stupid bastard.

619
01:01:21,561 --> 01:01:25,520
Bullshit. Bullshit. That's it.

620
01:01:25,698 --> 01:01:28,690
Enough is enough is enough.
I'm bloody sick of it.

621
01:01:29,035 --> 01:01:32,937
That fucker tried to put a 6-foot spear
through my scrotum...

622
01:01:33,473 --> 01:01:36,101
...and that is not something
I'm gonna forget in a hurry.

623
01:01:36,476 --> 01:01:37,841
Now come on, everybody.

624
01:01:38,311 --> 01:01:40,802
- Let's go do the bastard!
- You are right, Dmitry.

625
01:01:40,980 --> 01:01:44,677
It is time to make a stand and fight.
We are Russian.

626
01:02:01,100 --> 01:02:03,091
That's it. Quickly.

627
01:02:03,669 --> 01:02:05,569
Put him on the altar.

628
01:02:10,076 --> 01:02:13,102
Not like that. The other way.

629
01:02:26,192 --> 01:02:30,526
Almighty, accept this sacrifice
from your humble servant.

630
01:02:31,130 --> 01:02:35,760
Forgive my younger brother's foolishness.
He knows not what he does.

631
01:02:35,935 --> 01:02:38,096
What are you doing?

632
01:02:38,438 --> 01:02:41,737
To think I was speaking to the Almighty
on your behalf!

633
01:02:41,908 --> 01:02:46,106
You do too much speaking. I killed him.
I should be able to do whatever I like.

634
01:02:46,279 --> 01:02:48,713
If it was not for me,
you would be nothing.

635
01:02:48,881 --> 01:02:50,212
- But I skin...
- But nothing.

636
01:02:50,383 --> 01:02:52,044
- Apologize now!
- But I...

637
01:02:52,218 --> 01:02:53,549
Say you're sorry!

638
01:03:01,093 --> 01:03:02,788
Sorry.

639
01:03:05,631 --> 01:03:09,032
It doesn't matter anymore.
You ruined this one.

640
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:10,794
Get me another one.

641
01:03:15,775 --> 01:03:18,403
So, Dmitry, you ever thought about
career in army?

642
01:03:18,578 --> 01:03:22,105
I don't know. Is there an accelerated
promotion scheme for graduates?

643
01:03:27,720 --> 01:03:29,620
Are we leaving?

644
01:03:32,558 --> 01:03:34,549
- Yeah. I gotta get that cross.
- Ritchie...

645
01:03:34,727 --> 01:03:38,754
Look. I'm not gonna argue with you
about it. I'm sorry.

646
01:03:40,132 --> 01:03:41,258
Are you coming?

647
01:03:41,801 --> 01:03:46,238
- It's better if we stick together.
- Me and Dmitry have our own plans.

648
01:03:46,405 --> 01:03:48,396
Time to make our declaration of war.

649
01:03:48,808 --> 01:03:51,936
And we shall start here with this room.

650
01:03:53,913 --> 01:03:55,676
Good luck, guys.

651
01:03:56,315 --> 01:03:57,873
Good luck, Anna.

652
01:04:01,954 --> 01:04:03,421
Wait.

653
01:04:03,689 --> 01:04:06,021
Just gotta figure out
which is the right way.

654
01:04:06,192 --> 01:04:09,787
- Oh, it's not cramp, then.
- No.

655
01:04:10,429 --> 01:04:11,919
Thanks for staying with me.

656
01:04:12,098 --> 01:04:14,623
What was I going to do?
Run away with Boris?

657
01:04:16,335 --> 01:04:19,793
Look, I'm sorry I got you involved
in all this.

658
01:04:20,473 --> 01:04:23,465
Since I came back to Russia,
things haven't gone exactly to plan.

659
01:04:23,643 --> 01:04:26,612
It's time for a new plan.
We stick together...

660
01:04:26,779 --> 01:04:30,340
...we get out of here alive. Deal?

661
01:04:30,683 --> 01:04:32,310
Deal.

662
01:04:32,485 --> 01:04:35,283
- This way.
- No, it's that way.

663
01:04:36,022 --> 01:04:38,081
No, we're going back
to where Peter was shot.

664
01:04:38,257 --> 01:04:41,283
I know, that's why we should
go this way.

665
01:04:42,361 --> 01:04:44,659
Are you sure?
I think that's doubling back around.

666
01:04:44,830 --> 01:04:46,695
No, it's not.

667
01:04:46,999 --> 01:04:50,332
Look, you've made enough
bad choices for one day.

668
01:04:51,304 --> 01:04:52,635
Okay.

669
01:05:37,116 --> 01:05:38,743
Ritchie.

670
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:44,088
- It's stuck.
- All right. Hold on. Hold on.

671
01:05:44,256 --> 01:05:46,451
I can't pull it out.

672
01:05:48,861 --> 01:05:52,592
That son of a bitch. Okay.

673
01:05:54,500 --> 01:05:58,061
All right, it's gone through your ear
and it's opened up inside the wall.

674
01:05:58,237 --> 01:05:59,966
I'm not gonna be able to pull it out.

675
01:06:01,140 --> 01:06:02,402
What can we do?

676
01:06:04,644 --> 01:06:07,238
Okay, everything's gonna be okay.

677
01:06:07,413 --> 01:06:10,109
I'm not going anywhere,
but we can't stay here.

678
01:06:10,282 --> 01:06:12,842
You're gonna need to move your head
as quick as you can.

679
01:06:13,019 --> 01:06:15,283
- Get it over and done as fast as possible.
- What?

680
01:06:16,288 --> 01:06:19,451
- Do you understand me?
- You want me to tear half my ear off?

681
01:06:19,625 --> 01:06:22,560
- Oh, I can't.
- Yes, you can.

682
01:06:23,963 --> 01:06:25,760
Try for me.

683
01:06:29,669 --> 01:06:33,503
- I can't do it. I can't do it.
- Okay, fine. Shh, shh, shh.

684
01:06:33,806 --> 01:06:36,297
All right. Hey. Hey. Hey. Relax.

685
01:06:36,842 --> 01:06:38,935
Tell me about your favorite vacation.

686
01:06:39,111 --> 01:06:41,944
- What?
- Talk to me, okay?

687
01:06:44,016 --> 01:06:45,847
I don't know.

688
01:06:46,285 --> 01:06:51,313
- I suppose it would have to be Sochi.
- Sochi, yeah?

689
01:06:51,757 --> 01:06:57,024
- What's so good about that place?
- It's just really perfect.

690
01:06:58,497 --> 01:06:59,930
- I'm sorry.
- Aah!

691
01:07:03,903 --> 01:07:05,530
This will do.

692
01:07:54,019 --> 01:07:55,680
We didn't have much time.

693
01:07:58,124 --> 01:08:02,322
Considering everything, we did very well.

694
01:08:02,528 --> 01:08:06,089
- Think it will work?
- Of course, Dmitry.

695
01:08:06,265 --> 01:08:07,823
I mean...

696
01:08:08,634 --> 01:08:10,568
Do you think so?

697
01:08:11,203 --> 01:08:13,763
One hundred percent positive.

698
01:08:15,207 --> 01:08:16,697
Me too.

699
01:08:52,578 --> 01:08:54,239
Bastards!

700
01:09:06,759 --> 01:09:08,784
We're never going to get out of here.

701
01:09:08,961 --> 01:09:11,953
Nobody ever gets out of here.
Why should we be any different?

702
01:09:12,131 --> 01:09:16,261
Because we're different now.
Because we're together, we're a team.

703
01:09:16,468 --> 01:09:20,199
Come on, I need you to be as strong as
you already proved you were back there.

704
01:09:21,073 --> 01:09:24,304
Look, Anna, you gotta trust me.

705
01:09:24,476 --> 01:09:27,445
There's no way in hell
I'm letting either one of us die.

706
01:09:27,613 --> 01:09:30,741
We made a deal
to get out of here alive, right?

707
01:09:31,183 --> 01:09:33,310
I'm not in the business
of breaking my word.

708
01:09:45,097 --> 01:09:48,533
Did your mama never tell you
to keep your room tidy?

709
01:09:50,269 --> 01:09:53,363
I had him. Goddamn it.

710
01:09:55,441 --> 01:09:56,908
Fuck.

711
01:10:06,518 --> 01:10:08,918
He's been watching us the whole time.

712
01:10:11,323 --> 01:10:12,950
Hold this.

713
01:10:41,353 --> 01:10:42,820
Dmitry.

714
01:11:25,464 --> 01:11:27,022
Come on.

715
01:11:34,740 --> 01:11:36,537
Oh, no.

716
01:11:47,786 --> 01:11:49,583
Boris?

717
01:11:51,123 --> 01:11:52,249
Oh, fuck.

718
01:11:56,462 --> 01:11:58,293
Oh, fuck.

719
01:12:00,232 --> 01:12:02,496
I should have been an accountant.

720
01:12:04,136 --> 01:12:05,433
Oh, fuck.

721
01:12:34,967 --> 01:12:37,993
- My head.
